    <!--/tools-->
  
    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Irving Penn<br />
American, 1917–2009<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Cuzco Children, Cuzco, Peru</em>, 1948, printed December 1976</h3>

    <p>
    Platinum-palladium print, edition 28/60<br />    49.6 x 50.7 cm (image); 55.9 x 63.3 cm (paper)<br />    Inscribed verso: “CUZCO CHILDREN”; inscribed verso: “1369 [in a circle]”; inscribed verso: “BF 360 Paper on Aluminum / Multiple Coating and Printing / 1 [in a circle] Platinum / 2 [in a circle] Platinum-palladium / Print made December 1976”; signed and stamped verso: “Irving Penn / Hand-coated by the photographer [in a circle]”; stamped and inscribed verso: “In addition to 60 numbered prints of this image / in platinum metals, unnumbered, but signed, silver prints not exceeding a total of 30 may exist.”; inscribed verso: “28/60”; stamped and inscribed verso: “PHOTOGRAPH BY IRVING PENN / Copyright © 1960 by / THE CONDE NAST PUBLICATIONS INC. / Not to be reproduced without / written permission of the / copyright owner.”<br />    Restricted gift of Mrs. Leigh B. Block, 1977.913</p>
        Copyright Condé Nast Publications, Inc.
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

  </div>
  <!--/artwork-details-->

    
      <div id="artwork-body">
                <div id="abbrev">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/more" class="more">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
      <!--content hidden-->
    </div>
    <div id="extended">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/less" class="less">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
            <h2>Exhibition History</h2>
      <p>Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, “Irving Penn, A Career in Photography,” November 22, 1997–February 1, 1998; traveled to St. Petersburg, Russia, State Hermitage Museum, March 1–May 16, 1998; Hamburg, Germany, Deichtorhallen, June 18–September 6, 1998; Munich, Germany, Müchner Stadtmuseum, October 6, 1998–February 21, 1999; San Francisco, California, Friends of Photography/Ansel Adams Center for Photography, November 11, 1999–January 23, 2000; Museum of Fine Arts, Houston, March 25–June 4, 2000; Paris, France, Maison Européenne de la Photographie, September 13–November 5, 2000. (Colin Westerbeck)<br />
<br />
Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, "Far from Home: Photography, Travel, and Inspiration," January 20–May 6, 2007. (Elizabeth Siegel and Newell G. Smith)<br />
<br />
Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, “In the Vernacular,” February 6–May 31, 2010. (Greg Harris)</p>
                  <h2>Publication History</h2>
      <p>Penn, Irving. 1960. “Moments Preserved.” Simon and Schuster. p. 99. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Lyons, Nathan. 1967. "Photography in the Twentieth Century." Exh. cat. National Gallery of Canada/George Eastman House. p. 56. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Penn, Irving. 1974. “Worlds in a Small Room.” Grossman Publishers. p. 13. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Galleria Civica d’Arte Moderna, Turin. 1975. “I platini di Irving Penn: 25 anni di fotografia.” Exh. cat. Galleria Civica d’Arte Moderna/Ages Arti Grafiche. p. 29. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Marlborough Gallery, New York. 1977. “Irving Penn: Photographs in Platinum Metals, Images 1947–1975.” Exh. cat. Marlborough Gallery. n.pag., cat. 78. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Nash, Graham. 1978. "The Graham Nash Collection." Exh. cat. de Saisset Art Gallery and Museum/Nash Press. p. 68, fig. 114. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Szarkowski, John. 1984. "Irving Penn." Exh. cat. Museum of Modern Art/New York Graphic Society Books. pl. 59. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Pace/MacGill Gallery, New York. 1990. “Other Ways of Being: 100 Photographs, 1948–1971.” Exh. cat. Pace/MacGill Gallery. pl. 4. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Penn, Irving. 1991. "Passage: A Work Record." Knopf. p. 61. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Fraser, Kennedy. 1992. “On the Edge: Images from 100 Years of Vogue.” Exh. cat. New York Public Library/Random House. p. 79. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Westerbeck, Colin. 1997. “Irving Penn: A Career in Photography.” Exh. cat. Art Institute of Chicago/Bulfinch Press. p. 177, cat. 37.<br />
<br />
Penn, Irving. 2004. “A Notebook at Random.” Bulfinch Press. p. 91. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Greenough, Sarah. 2005. “Irving Penn: Platinum Prints.” Exh. cat. National Gallery of Art/Yale University Press. pl. 15. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Bernheimer Fine Art Photography, Munich . 2011. “Irving Penn: Ethnos.” Exh. cat. Bernheimer Fine Art Photography. pl. 15. (other print of this image)</p>
                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Marlborough Gallery, New York [then the artist's representative], by September 1977; sold to the Art Institute, 1977.</p>
